item.description: I’m a Microsoft Research PhD Scholar in the Department of Computer Science, University College London, UK. I’m supervised by Daniel C. Alexander of the Centre for Medical Image Computing and Antonio Criminisi of Microsoft Research Cambridge. My research focuses on developing high-performance machine learning algorithms which are interpretable, robust and safe to use in medical applications. During my Phd, I have had the fortune to get involved in startups at different stages of maturity.
